-- Bond Risk Climbs to Five-Week High in Europe on Tapering Concern
-- B y   N a t a s h a   D o f f
-- 2013-08-20T08:13:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-20/bond-risk-climbs-to-five-week-high-in-europe-on-tapering-concern.html
The cost of insuring corporate bonds
against losses rose for a second day in Europe on investor
concern the Federal Reserve will start curbing asset purchases
as soon as next month.  The Markit iTraxx Europe Index of credit-default swaps on
125 companies with investment-grade ratings gained 1.2 basis
points to 104 basis points at 9:11 a.m in  London , the highest
level since July 17. The average yield on the debt climbed 4
basis points to a six-week high of 2.1 percent, according to
Bloomberg  bond index  data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natasha Doff in London at 
